# üîµ REACT ROUTING (React Router) ‚Äì INTERVIEW QUESTIONS WITH ANSWERS & CODE

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ What is React Router?

React Router is a **client-side routing library** used to build **Single Page Applications (SPA)** in React.

‚û°Ô∏è It changes UI **without reloading the page**.

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Why do we need Routing in React?

* Multiple pages without page refresh
* Better user experience
* URL-based navigation
* SPA behavior

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ What is SPA (Single Page Application)?

An application where:

* Only **one HTML page** loads
* Content updates dynamically using JavaScript

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Which package is used for routing in React?

```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```

---

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ What are the core components of React Router?

* **BrowserRouter**
* **Routes**
* **Route**
* **Link / NavLink**
* **useParams**
* **useNavigate**
* **useLocation**

---

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ What is BrowserRouter?

It enables routing using **HTML5 history API**.

```jsx
import { BrowserRouter } from "react-router-dom";

<BrowserRouter>
  <App />
</BrowserRouter>
```

---

## 7Ô∏è‚É£ What is Routes?

`Routes` is a wrapper that contains all `Route` components.

```jsx
<Routes>
  <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
</Routes>
```

---

## 8Ô∏è‚É£ What is Route?

Defines **path ‚Üí component mapping**.

```jsx
<Route path="/about" element={<About />} />
```

---

## 9Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between Routes & Route?

| Routes             | Route             |
| ------------------ | ----------------- |
| Wraps routes       | Defines path      |
| Matches best route | Renders component |

---

## üîü What is Link?

Used for navigation **without page reload**.

```jsx
<Link to="/about">About</Link>
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between Link & anchor (`<a>`) tag?

| Link           | `<a>`       |
| -------------- | ----------- |
| SPA navigation | Page reload |
| Faster         | Slower      |

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ What is NavLink?

Same as Link but supports **active styling**.

```jsx
<NavLink 
  to="/home"
  className={({ isActive }) => isActive ? "active" : ""}
>
  Home
</NavLink>
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ What is useNavigate?

Used for **programmatic navigation**.

```jsx
const navigate = useNavigate();
navigate("/login");
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ When do you use useNavigate?

* After form submit
* After login/logout
* Redirect logic

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is useParams?

Used to read **URL parameters**.

```jsx
<Route path="/user/:id" element={<User />} />
```

```jsx
const { id } = useParams();
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ What is useLocation?

Gives current route info.

```jsx
const location = useLocation();
console.log(location.pathname);
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ What is Dynamic Routing?

Routing based on dynamic values.

```jsx
/product/:productId
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ What is Nested Routing?

Routing inside another route.

```jsx
<Route path="/dashboard" element={<Dashboard />}>
  <Route path="profile" element={<Profile />} />
  <Route path="settings" element={<Settings />} />
</Route>
```

```jsx
<Outlet />
```

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ What is Outlet?

Renders **child route component**.

```jsx
import { Outlet } from "react-router-dom";
<Outlet />
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ What is Index Route?

Default route inside nested routes.

```jsx
<Route index element={<DashboardHome />} />
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Protected Route?

Restricts access based on auth.

```jsx
const PrivateRoute = ({ children }) => {
  const isAuth = true;
  return isAuth ? children : <Navigate to="/login" />;
};
```

```jsx
<Route path="/admin" element={
  <PrivateRoute>
    <Admin />
  </PrivateRoute>
} />
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ What is Navigate?

Used for redirection.

```jsx
<Navigate to="/login" />
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ Redirect vs Navigate?

‚ùå Redirect (removed)
‚úÖ Navigate (React Router v6)

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ How to handle 404 Page?

```jsx
<Route path="*" element={<NotFound />} />
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is useSearchParams?

Used for **query parameters**.

```jsx
const [params] = useSearchParams();
params.get("q");
```

URL:

```
/search?q=react
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between Params & Query Params?

| Params   | Query    |
| -------- | -------- |
| /user/1  | ?id=1    |
| Required | Optional |

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ Lazy Loading Routes?

Improves performance.

```jsx
const Home = React.lazy(() => import("./Home"));

<Suspense fallback={<Loader />}>
  <Home />
</Suspense>
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ What is Code Splitting in Routing?

Loading route code **only when needed**.

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ How does React Router work internally?

* Uses History API
* Listens to URL changes
* Matches route tree

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between React Router v5 & v6?

| v5        | v6         |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Switch    | Routes     |
| component | element    |
| exact     | auto exact |

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ What is exact in v6?

‚ùå Not required
Routes are **exact by default**

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Can we use multiple routers?

‚ùå No (avoid nesting BrowserRouter)

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ How to pass state during navigation?

```jsx
navigate("/profile", { state: { name: "Palash" } });
```

```jsx
const location = useLocation();
location.state.name;
```

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ What is basename?

Used when app is deployed in subfolder.

```jsx
<BrowserRouter basename="/app">
```

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ Common Routing Mistakes

‚ùå Using `<a>` instead of Link
‚ùå Not handling 404
‚ùå No lazy loading
‚ùå Storing auth logic inside component

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ Folder Structure (Recommended)

```
src/
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ routes/
 ‚îÇ    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ AppRoutes.jsx
 ‚îÇ    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ PrivateRoute.jsx
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pages/
 ‚îÇ    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Home.jsx
 ‚îÇ    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Login.jsx
```

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ Can routing replace backend auth?

‚ùå NO
Frontend routing is **not security**

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ Performance Optimization

* Lazy routes
* Avoid re-renders
* Memoize layouts

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ Interview One-Liner

"React Router enables SPA navigation using URL-based routing without page reload."

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ MUST-PRACTICE BEFORE INTERVIEW

‚úÖ Dynamic routes
‚úÖ Protected routes
‚úÖ Nested routes
‚úÖ useNavigate
‚úÖ useParams
‚úÖ Lazy loading

